<description>His father was a French international and Youri began his career at Grenoble where he stayed until moving to Strasbourg in 1989. After only a season and a half he left for Monaco where he won a French Cup Winners medal and reached the final of the European Cup Winnerï¿½s Cup. 
 Youri won international recognition while at Monaco making his debut in October 1993 against Israel. He moved to Paris St Germain for the 1995-96 season winning a European Cup Winners Cup medal in that one season. 
 Youri starred at Euro 1996 where his performances earned him a move to Inter. 
 He could have moved to Manchester United but decided to join Kaiserslautern who had offered him a longer contract. He fell out with coach Andy Brehme and was forced to join Bolton Wanderers in the 2001-02 season in an attempt to make the World Cup Final squad. 
 A gifted attacking midfielder, Youri joined Blackburn Rovers in September 2004 with a three-month contract.</description>

